till occasionally found.  St Nicholas  was a 4th-century bishop of Myra in Lycia, about whom virtually nothing factual is known, although a vast body of legend grew up around him, and he became the patron saint of Greece and of Russia, as well as of children, sailors, merchants, and pawnbrokers. His feast day is  6 December , and among the many roles which legend has assigned to him is that of bringer of Christmas presents, in the guise of ‘Santa Claus’ (an alteration of the Dutch form of his name, <i>Sinterklaas</i>)."],"variants":[{"name":"Nickolas","meanings":["Mainly U.S.: variant spelling of   Nicholas  , influenced by the short form   Nick ."]},{"name":"Nicolas","meanings":["From Late Greek.  See  <b>Nicholas</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs Nicholas de Shelton was born about 1201, in Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 2 sons with Nicholas De Shelton 6th Lord Shelton."},"et":{"Abt 1201–":"umbes 1201–Surnud","1203–1257":"1203–1257","1211–1271":"1211–1271","1227–Male":"1227–Surnud","1201–Female":"1201–Surnud","1227":"1227","1203":"1203","Abt 1201":"umbes 1201","1257":"1257","1201":"1201","1211":"1211","about 1227":"umbes 1227","about 1211":"umbes 1211","1271":"1271","Shelton, Norfolk, England":"Shelton, Norfolk, England","Stradbroke, Suffolk, England":"Stradbroke, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom",", Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1201–":"noin 1201–Kuollut","1203–1257":"1203–1257","1211–1271":"1211–1271","1227–Male":"1227–Kuollut","1201–Female":"1201–Kuollut","1227":"1227","1203":"1203","Abt 1201":"noin 1201","1257":"1257","1201":"1201","1211":"1211","about 1227":"noin 1227","about 1211":"noin 1211","1271":"1271","Shelton, Norfolk, England":"Shelton, Norfolk, England","Stradbroke, Suffolk, England":"Stradbroke, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta",", Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1201–":"environ 1201–Décédée","1203–1257":"1203–1257","1211–1271":"1211–1271","